Package RuleEngine

Class AbstractProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • RuleEngine.AbstractProcessor
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AssignmentProcessor, ConceptAttributeFunctionalProcessor, ConceptAttributeRelationalProcessor, ConceptProcessor, DataAttributeFunctionalMultipleProcessor, DataAttributeFunctionalSingleProcessor, DataAttributeRelationalProcessor, FilterProcessor, JunctorProcessor, PeekProcessor, QuantificationProcessor, SequenceProcessor, TransferProcessor

    public abstract class AbstractProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the top class for all processors. It provides a number of auxiliary methods to be used in the subclasses.

      • getOutputStream

        public java.util.stream.Stream<java.lang.Object[]> getOutputStream​()
        returns the output stream. This method must be overwritten in the sub-classes. The stream itself must be generated in the overwritten method and stored in outputStream. Afterwardes the overwritten method should call super.getOutputStream(). super.getOutputStream() may add a peek-operation to the output stream which prints the current contents of the query array to System.out.
        Returns:
        the output stream.
